<h1>Problem 2041 - Mocktest Geometry Olympiad MGO 2024, P1 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(I\) be the incenter of \(\triangle ABC\). Let \(l\) be an arbitary line
passing through \(I\). \(l\) intersects \((ABC)\) at points \(X\) and \(Y\) and intersects \(BC\) at
\(Z\). The line through \(Z\) parallel to \(AI\) intersects \(AX\) and \(AY\) at \(D\) and \(E\) respectively.
Prove that points \(A, I, D, E\) are concyclic.</p>
